# adigator-generated derivative files (forward / reverse / J'·v) + their data.
# These are produced next to the source by adigatorGen*; never commit them.
*_ADiGator*.m
*_ADiGator*.mat
*_Jac.m
*_Hes.m
*_Grd.m
*_RGrd.m
*_JtV.m
*_RGrd.mat
*_JtV.mat
adigatortempfunc*.m

# MATLAB Coder / build output (codegen examples, SCodegenTest, R15 codegen-equiv).
codegen/
codegen_lib/
slprj/
*_mex.*
*.mexa64
*.mexw64
*.mexmaca64
*.mexmaci64

# Editor / MATLAB autosave cruft.
*.asv

# Per-example scratch dirs for adigator-generated example output (issue #67/#69).
examples/**/generated/

# Intentional, committed generated-shaped fixtures (synthetic + offline-test
# fixtures): keep them — and any future ones — trackable without `git add -f`.
# Must stay last so it overrides the suffix rules above.
!tests/fixtures/**
